'''Jevargi''' is a [[panchayat town]] in [[Gulbarga district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Karnataka]].

==Geography==
Jevargi is located at {{coor d|17.02|N|76.77|E|}}<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/19/Jevargi.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Jevargi]</ref>. It has an average elevation of 393&nbsp;[[metre]]s (1289&nbsp;[[foot (unit of length)|feet]]).

==Demographics==
[[As of 2001]] India [[census]]{{GR|India}}, Jevargi had a population of 19,174. Males constitute 51% of the population and females 49%. Jevargi has an average literacy rate of 53%, lower than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 63%, and female literacy is 43%. In Jevargi, 17% of the population is under 6 years of age.

